WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:37.497 --> 00:00:39.040
Any sign of them?

3
00:00:45.963 --> 00:00:47.632
Shall we continue south. Arkaan?

4
00:00:47.757 --> 00:00:50.718
The other hunters will all head south.

5
00:01:00.687 --> 00:01:02.105
We shall go west.

6
00:01:08.903 --> 00:01:10.613
Thank you all for joining me.

7
00:01:10.738 --> 00:01:12.948
I have discovered
something very interesting.

8
00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:14.367
We. we discovered.

9
00:01:14.658 --> 00:01:15.535
This is it.

10
00:01:16.035 --> 00:01:17.537
The answer to our problems.

11
00:01:17.662 --> 00:01:18.412
Wow.

12
00:01:18.580 --> 00:01:19.663
A treasure map?

13
00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:22.458
And I thought Flynn was
the only one playing prospector.

14
00:01:22.583 --> 00:01:23.250
Actually. I--

15
00:01:23.375 --> 00:01:25.378
It's not just any
treasure. this is Oleg's keep.

16
00:01:25.503 --> 00:01:27.588
The mountain fortress of
the last king of the dwarves.

17
00:01:27.713 --> 00:01:28.380
Please.

18
00:01:28.840 --> 00:01:31.550
That place has been picked and
pillaged by fortune hunters for centuries.

19
00:01:31.675 --> 00:01:35.222
But no one. not even me.
has ever found the real prize.

20
00:01:35.347 --> 00:01:38.223
The legendary crown of King Oleg himself.

21
00:01:38.348 --> 00:01:40.852
Because none of us knew about this.

22
00:01:43.855 --> 00:01:45.063
Pretty cool. huh?

23
00:01:47.733 --> 00:01:50.195
You found a secret underground vault.

24
00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:51.612
I must say I'm impressed. Calibor.

25
00:01:51.737 --> 00:01:52.322
I found it. actually.

26
00:01:52.447 --> 00:01:54.990
With this treasure. I can trade
for all the maro the void key requires.

27
00:01:55.115 --> 00:01:59.120
We. we. can
trade it. because I found it.

28
00:01:59.245 --> 00:02:02.082
And you really believe
that your Uzek friend will deliver?

29
00:02:02.207 --> 00:02:03.875
The pirate and gambling fiend.

30
00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:05.668
Pirates. yes. gambler. absolutely.

31
00:02:05.793 --> 00:02:08.378
But unlike most
Uzeks. once his word is given.

32
00:02:08.505 --> 00:02:10.382
Riplakish always comes through.

33
00:02:10.507 --> 00:02:12.175
Not always how you
think. but he gets it done.

34
00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:14.260
And that'll be enough
maro to get us home. right?

35
00:02:14.385 --> 00:02:14.927
All of us.

36
00:02:15.052 --> 00:02:17.430
It will be more than enough
to get you three back to your world.

37
00:02:17.555 --> 00:02:20.642
And me. along with you.
to ensure the Skull is destroyed.

38
00:02:20.767 --> 00:02:21.267
For good.

39
00:02:21.392 --> 00:02:24.103
Sure. okay. you had me at.
we get to go home. so...

40
00:02:24.228 --> 00:02:24.937
Where is this keep?

41
00:02:25.062 --> 00:02:25.563
The northern kipch.

42
00:02:25.688 --> 00:02:27.190
The northern kingdom.

43
00:02:27.565 --> 00:02:31.443
Hey. dude. Calibor is
trying to explain to us his plan. okay?

44
00:02:31.568 --> 00:02:32.153
I know. it's just that...

45
00:02:32.278 --> 00:02:33.613
The northern
kingdom is a three-day journey.

46
00:02:33.738 --> 00:02:36.323
I'll head into Tyr-Valen
today to arrange supplies.

47
00:02:36.448 --> 00:02:39.952
I'll inform the clerics that
tonight will be our last at Tyr-Valen.

48
00:02:40.077 --> 00:02:42.163
We'll leave tomorrow at dawn.

49
00:02:43.582 --> 00:02:44.540
Well done. Calibor.

50
00:02:44.665 --> 00:02:45.708
Thank you so much.

51
00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:46.918
You're the man.

52
00:02:47.252 --> 00:02:48.335
What is your problem?

53
00:02:51.505 --> 00:02:52.173
Hello?

54
00:02:54.342 --> 00:02:56.970
No big deal. just me being legendary.

55
00:03:22.662 --> 00:03:29.668
I'm a little lost.
but you know I'm not afraid.

56
00:03:41.097 --> 00:03:44.933
All my life got crossed.
and I will never be the same.

57
00:04:01.325 --> 00:04:07.248
And now we're all a little
lost. but you know I'm not afraid.

58
00:04:41.365 --> 00:04:45.787
Yesterday I was just fooling
around. Today. you're going down.

59
00:04:51.083 --> 00:04:52.585
Ah. right in the hand.

60
00:04:53.543 --> 00:04:56.463
So when did you stop
letting him beat the snot out of you?

61
00:04:56.588 --> 00:04:59.175
Oh. hey. I'm just going easy on him.

62
00:04:59.342 --> 00:05:01.968
You know. I don't want to poke
the bear. You know. literally.

63
00:05:02.095 --> 00:05:03.012
Is this true?

64
00:05:03.595 --> 00:05:06.307
Because Kavan was
also going easy on Cash.

65
00:05:06.432 --> 00:05:07.475
Seriously?

66
00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:09.143
Kavan will now use full strength.

67
00:05:09.685 --> 00:05:12.397
Oh. wow. Yeah. great. you do that.

68
00:05:22.657 --> 00:05:26.077
Kavan. please try
not to kill him.

69
00:05:26.702 --> 00:05:30.122
This is how Kavan's
clan trains small children.

70
00:05:32.667 --> 00:05:34.543
It's time to show you
how it's done in my world.

71
00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:37.297
Bottom of the ninth. let's play ball.

72
00:05:38.672 --> 00:05:41.175
This is not how Kavan
taught you to hold your weapon.

73
00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:44.387
Yeah. well. so far
your instructions get me cooked.

74
00:05:44.512 --> 00:05:47.515
I had a homer against
Fairview like last year with this grip.

75
00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:49.183
so why don't I
just stick with what I know?

76
00:05:49.308 --> 00:05:52.103
Who is this homer exactly that you hit?

77
00:05:52.812 --> 00:05:55.648
It's baseball. I play in the off-season.

78
00:05:59.110 --> 00:06:01.403
He's just trying to impress you.

79
00:06:01.653 --> 00:06:02.363
Oh. yeah.

80
00:06:11.663 --> 00:06:13.207
Come at me. bro.

81
00:06:13.665 --> 00:06:18.670
Kavan begs you to hold your weapon like an
actual warrior. Bro.

82
00:06:18.797 --> 00:06:20.047
Don't bro me. bro.

83
00:06:20.172 --> 00:06:23.258
Okay. I got a
bigger swing radius this way.

84
00:06:23.467 --> 00:06:27.513
That might not compute in.
like. your little barbarian brain.

85
00:06:27.638 --> 00:06:30.475
But you're just going to have to
learn the hard way.

86
00:06:40.902 --> 00:06:42.653
Oh!

87
00:06:43.695 --> 00:06:44.572
Whoa

88
00:06:50.995 --> 00:06:54.248
Aurora. how about some
of that magic healing touch?

89
00:06:54.373 --> 00:06:56.083
Everything hurts so bad.

90
00:06:56.333 --> 00:06:59.337
Alleviating mere
discomfort is a waste of maro.

91
00:06:59.462 --> 00:07:01.213
Yeah. walk it off. slugger.

92
00:07:01.338 --> 00:07:03.548
None of this makes any sense.

93
00:07:03.673 --> 00:07:05.510
I should be great at this.

94
00:07:06.135 --> 00:07:07.010
How exactly?

95
00:07:07.887 --> 00:07:10.013
Because I'm good at everything.

96
00:07:10.138 --> 00:07:10.723
I'm sorry.

97
00:07:10.848 --> 00:07:12.767
Well. everything I try at--

98
00:07:12.933 --> 00:07:14.810
it's not just sports. I get good grades.

99
00:07:14.935 --> 00:07:16.145
I got the lead in the play.

100
00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:17.355
No. no. no. no.

101
00:07:19.232 --> 00:07:20.817
Look. the teachers give you good grades

102
00:07:20.942 --> 00:07:24.195
because they can't be the reason
that Mr. Football gets cut from the team.

103
00:07:24.320 --> 00:07:26.697
And the only reason
you got Danny Zuko in Greece

104
00:07:26.822 --> 00:07:30.158
is because you
slumming it puts butts in seats.

105
00:07:31.827 --> 00:07:33.453
It's not the right day to mess with me.

106
00:07:35.205 --> 00:07:36.665
You are messing with me. right?

107
00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:39.293
Look. sports are easy for you.

108
00:07:40.545 --> 00:07:42.172
Everything else is only easy for you

109
00:07:42.297 --> 00:07:45.883
because the people
around you make it easy on you.

110
00:07:46.217 --> 00:07:49.928
In this world. no one
even knows what a football is.

111
00:07:51.222 --> 00:07:52.723
That's not-- no.

112
00:07:54.808 --> 00:07:55.893
No. no. no. no.

113
00:07:58.187 --> 00:07:58.855
Oh. no.

114
00:08:02.317 --> 00:08:05.612
Oh. no. no. no.
That's it. I'm out. I'm out.

115
00:08:06.195 --> 00:08:08.322
Out? Seriously?

116
00:08:08.865 --> 00:08:12.075
Yeah. it's time for
a break from all of this.

117
00:08:12.285 --> 00:08:14.995
I'll be in town
with Calibor if you need me.

118
00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:18.040
So the first thing that doesn't
come naturally to you. you what. quit?

119
00:08:18.165 --> 00:08:19.667
Does it even matter?

120
00:08:19.792 --> 00:08:21.543
We already have Kavan.
He's the real warrior.

121
00:08:21.668 --> 00:08:25.757
Like. who says you need me anyways?

122
00:08:25.882 --> 00:08:28.675
Just a mystical prophecy. no big.

123
00:08:29.552 --> 00:08:30.762
Yo. Calibor.

124
00:08:30.970 --> 00:08:32.347
What just happened?

125
00:08:32.888 --> 00:08:34.015
I broke the guy.

126
00:08:35.558 --> 00:08:37.810
It's okay. He'll come around.

127
00:08:40.563 --> 00:08:42.273
First door on the right.

128
00:08:43.857 --> 00:08:44.525
Hey!

129
00:08:47.862 --> 00:08:49.988
Do we need to get her some aspirin?

130
00:08:50.113 --> 00:08:52.073
Or a straight jacket or something?

131
00:08:52.198 --> 00:08:55.452
I have no idea.
Everything she does freaks me out.

132
00:08:55.578 --> 00:08:57.788
I'm just as clueless about her as you are.

133
00:08:58.163 --> 00:08:59.123
Doubt it.

134
00:08:59.790 --> 00:09:01.500
You were pretty obsessed
with her yesterday on the field.

135
00:09:01.625 --> 00:09:03.335
before the game got canceled.

136
00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:06.797
I know. It's all weird.
but it's not like that.

137
00:09:07.340 --> 00:09:10.635
Look. I've just been
trying to figure her out.

138
00:09:11.010 --> 00:09:12.595
I mean. figure out what she's doing.

139
00:09:12.720 --> 00:09:13.637
Zaya is not my--

140
00:09:13.762 --> 00:09:16.932
Stop. Stop. You're
making it so much worse.

141
00:09:18.225 --> 00:09:22.355
Okay. listen. Whatever
Zaya is. she is your problem.

142
00:09:22.480 --> 00:09:23.605
So if she barfs in my car.

143
00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:27.025
you are personally
detailing every inch of it.

144
00:09:33.865 --> 00:09:34.533
Found it!

145
00:09:34.658 --> 00:09:37.160
What is--
What is wrong with you?

146
00:09:37.287 --> 00:09:38.787
Found it. Found what?

147
00:09:39.330 --> 00:09:42.833
Inside the fortress.
there is a locked door.

148
00:09:43.667 --> 00:09:46.962
Behind that is a
collection of confiscated objects.

149
00:09:47.087 --> 00:09:48.505
Confiscated objects?

150
00:09:48.965 --> 00:09:50.548
Like an evidence room?

151
00:09:50.842 --> 00:09:54.345
Inside the room is the object
we need to bring your brother home.

152
00:09:54.553 --> 00:09:56.847
Hi. Home from where exactly?

153
00:09:56.972 --> 00:10:00.350
Uh. let's not get into
that right now. It's a whole thing.

154
00:10:00.475 --> 00:10:02.562
So how do we get this object?

155
00:10:03.437 --> 00:10:06.648
Not we. Darryl. It must be you.

156
00:10:15.700 --> 00:10:16.825
Hey!

157
00:10:17.368 --> 00:10:19.787
Wait! I'm coming with you guys.

158
00:10:20.078 --> 00:10:21.872
Absolutely not. One
of you is torture enough.

159
00:10:21.997 --> 00:10:23.915
Look. the only reason Cash is coming

160
00:10:24.042 --> 00:10:26.460
is because Oaklee
dropped a truth bomb on him.

161
00:10:26.585 --> 00:10:28.503
and he's having an existential crisis.

162
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:30.547
Like he said. You're not invited.

163
00:10:30.840 --> 00:10:34.093
I found the map. I should
be helping you guys make this plan.

164
00:10:34.218 --> 00:10:35.762
Help would imply
you have something to offer.

165
00:10:35.887 --> 00:10:38.888
I've beaten Skyrim.
the Witcher. Elden Ring.

166
00:10:39.015 --> 00:10:41.600
I have more tomb raid
and dungeon crawl experience

167
00:10:41.725 --> 00:10:42.852
than any one here.

168
00:10:42.977 --> 00:10:45.145
Oleg's Keep has
neither a tomb nor a dungeon.

169
00:10:45.270 --> 00:10:48.357
Then teach me. I gotta
learn from the best. right?

170
00:10:48.482 --> 00:10:51.777
I should be shadowing my
mentor's every move.

171
00:10:54.780 --> 00:10:56.573
You're right. You should.

172
00:10:57.032 --> 00:10:59.743
If I didn't think you were
ready for a mission of your own.

173
00:10:59.868 --> 00:11:00.660
You serious?

174
00:11:00.787 --> 00:11:06.208
Very. I have a quest that only you. my
esteemed apprentice. can accomplish.

175
00:11:06.667 --> 00:11:07.668
Done. Name it.

176
00:11:08.835 --> 00:11:09.753
Oh. sorry.

177
00:11:10.670 --> 00:11:13.548
It requires many items that
cannot be procured in the village.

178
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:17.762
so they must be tracked
down right here at the sanctuary.

179
00:11:20.723 --> 00:11:22.808
So you want me to
steal these from the clerics?

180
00:11:22.933 --> 00:11:25.560
Ah. steal. Such an ugly word. Borrow.

181
00:11:26.520 --> 00:11:28.147
There'll be payment
enough once we get the treasure.

182
00:11:28.272 --> 00:11:30.775
Besides. it's for the greater good.

183
00:11:31.650 --> 00:11:32.860
The greater good?

184
00:11:32.985 --> 00:11:33.652
Indeed.

185
00:11:35.070 --> 00:11:36.613
Unless you think
it's too difficult a task.

186
00:11:36.738 --> 00:11:38.948
No. no. no. Thank you for this.

187
00:11:39.658 --> 00:11:41.577
I won't let you down. boss.

188
00:11:42.787 --> 00:11:43.995
Off you go. then.

189
00:12:00.678 --> 00:12:02.807
Okay. Darryl. You got this.

190
00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:06.560
You're not crazy.
Just follow the instructions.

191
00:12:06.685 --> 00:12:10.773
and things will work out.
Just like with Wally and Libby.

192
00:12:22.660 --> 00:12:26.205
I can't give you any
information. It has to be a parent.

193
00:12:26.330 --> 00:12:29.250
Look. Sheriff Williams
said he'd be in touch with updates.

194
00:12:29.375 --> 00:12:30.667
but we haven't heard a thing.

195
00:12:30.793 --> 00:12:33.587
I understand. but like I said.
he's not in the office right now.

196
00:12:33.712 --> 00:12:36.798
Have your mom give
him a call and check in.

197
00:12:37.717 --> 00:12:38.925
Ah. okay. Thanks.

198
00:12:39.968 --> 00:12:42.805
Also. can I use your bathroom?

199
00:12:43.263 --> 00:12:45.473
We have a bathroom. It's not public.

200
00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:46.642
Please!

201
00:12:49.645 --> 00:12:52.438
Down the hall. third door on the right.

202
00:13:08.622 --> 00:13:09.540
What is this?

203
00:13:10.165 --> 00:13:11.167
It's my phone.

204
00:13:12.543 --> 00:13:14.253
Do you not have a phone?

205
00:13:18.048 --> 00:13:20.633
I mean. here. look. you
can like take pictures on it.

206
00:13:21.093 --> 00:13:22.970
If you want. we could like take a selfie.

207
00:13:23.095 --> 00:13:23.762
A selfie?

208
00:13:24.012 --> 00:13:25.263
So it's like. here. look.

209
00:13:25.388 --> 00:13:28.683
So you turn the
camera this way. and then see.

210
00:13:29.058 --> 00:13:32.605
See. that's you. and then we smile.

211
00:13:33.355 --> 00:13:35.900
And then like.
like. like cute. like. hmm.

212
00:13:36.025 --> 00:13:37.358
Yeah. yeah. there you go.

213
00:13:39.612 --> 00:13:41.572
Oh. I look really good in that one.

214
00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:55.502
What?

215
00:14:07.305 --> 00:14:08.640
Better start talking. kid.

216
00:14:09.683 --> 00:14:10.558
Wait. I--oh.

217
00:14:11.852 --> 00:14:13.562
Sorry?

218
00:14:16.732 --> 00:14:18.608
Oh. come on. guys. I swear.

219
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:20.443
I was just looking for the bathroom.

220
00:14:20.568 --> 00:14:22.947
Oh. hey. there it is. Can I go now?

221
00:14:23.072 --> 00:14:24.240
It's all a misunderstanding.

222
00:14:24.365 --> 00:14:26.658
You can explain it to your
mom when she comes to bail you out.

223
00:14:26.783 --> 00:14:28.077
Don't call my mom.

224
00:14:28.202 --> 00:14:30.913
Hey. Are you kidding me?

225
00:15:10.118 --> 00:15:11.245
Lasadh.

226
00:15:12.037 --> 00:15:15.540
Try again. Oaklee.
This time. use less maro.

227
00:15:17.583 --> 00:15:18.252
Focus.

228
00:15:21.630 --> 00:15:22.547
Lasadh.

229
00:15:27.135 --> 00:15:28.095
Too much maro.

230
00:15:28.220 --> 00:15:29.305
Still?

231
00:15:30.013 --> 00:15:32.223
I only used. like. three tiny specks.

232
00:15:32.348 --> 00:15:34.685
A single grain can light a bonfire.

233
00:15:34.810 --> 00:15:35.810
Maybe for you.

234
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:40.398
I didn't think this was gonna be so hard.

235
00:15:40.523 --> 00:15:42.400
We walk before we run.

236
00:15:43.652 --> 00:15:45.945
And we do not run in the sanctuary.

237
00:15:46.072 --> 00:15:49.992
I'm sorry. sister. I'm just
on a top-secret mission from Calibor.

238
00:15:50.117 --> 00:15:50.575
What is all that?

239
00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:53.037
I can't. I said too much already.

240
00:15:53.995 --> 00:15:58.583
What I can tell you is it is
vital that I outsmart the larder lady.

241
00:15:58.708 --> 00:16:01.420
Our raid on Oleg's Keep depends on it.

242
00:16:01.878 --> 00:16:03.088
I was never here.

243
00:16:03.213 --> 00:16:05.840
I'm so glad I have no
idea what he means by that.

244
00:16:05.965 --> 00:16:10.553
Focus. Oaklee. This here is
the last of your maro for the day.

245
00:16:13.973 --> 00:16:14.975
Your necklace.

246
00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:19.938
I've seen the symbols
in some of the books here.

247
00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:21.440
What's it mean?

248
00:16:22.775 --> 00:16:26.945
It's difficult to put into words.
but it represents our faith.

249
00:16:27.070 --> 00:16:28.072
Faith in what?

250
00:16:28.238 --> 00:16:33.410
Faith in life. Faith that even though we
struggle between darkness and light.

251
00:16:33.535 --> 00:16:37.038
we are working
together toward the greatest good.

252
00:16:37.455 --> 00:16:39.792
Doesn't that seem a little naive?

253
00:16:40.292 --> 00:16:42.795
Do not mistake cynicism for wisdom.

254
00:16:44.880 --> 00:16:47.717
Sometimes the long
journey to understanding takes

255
00:16:47.842 --> 00:16:50.552
you right back to
what you knew in the beginning.

256
00:16:50.677 --> 00:16:55.682
Yeah. well. I leave tomorrow and
I already know how to light a candle.

257
00:16:56.392 --> 00:16:59.812
And I'm not sure when
or if I'm gonna see you again.

258
00:16:59.937 --> 00:17:04.733
so there has got to be something else you
can teach me before I go.

259
00:17:05.525 --> 00:17:06.693
Very well.

260
00:17:11.157 --> 00:17:12.490
Here. what is it?

261
00:17:14.660 --> 00:17:16.078
Watch closely.

262
00:17:19.415 --> 00:17:20.248
Séideadh.

263
00:17:21.958 --> 00:17:24.252
Blowing out a candle. Thrilling.

264
00:17:25.045 --> 00:17:25.962
Lasadh.

265
00:17:28.507 --> 00:17:30.133
Go on. Your turn.

266
00:17:39.100 --> 00:17:39.768
Séideadh.

267
00:17:42.353 --> 00:17:43.480
Too much maro.

268
00:17:44.857 --> 00:17:45.940
Again.

269
00:17:56.993 --> 00:17:58.037
Stay close.

270
00:17:58.995 --> 00:18:02.540
This town has no love for Vedric. but no
doubt he’s put out a bounty on our heads

271
00:18:02.665 --> 00:18:05.252
which means he has eyes everywhere.

272
00:18:07.337 --> 00:18:09.590
Trust no one. Got it. So what's next?
You meeting someone?

273
00:18:09.715 --> 00:18:13.552
You're meeting someone.
My business is elsewhere in town.

274
00:18:13.677 --> 00:18:15.095
I'm meeting someone?

275
00:18:17.472 --> 00:18:18.390
Wait. what?

276
00:18:36.658 --> 00:18:38.118
Cash. meet Runa.

277
00:18:41.078 --> 00:18:41.747
Yo.

278
00:18:43.957 --> 00:18:47.793
I'll be back before sunset.
The boy drinks water only.

279
00:18:49.253 --> 00:18:51.382
Wait. you got me a babysitter?

280
00:18:53.008 --> 00:18:55.968
I'm not familiar with that word.
but you are essentially a helpless baby.

281
00:18:56.093 --> 00:18:59.890
and if you don't behave.
I approve of her sitting on you. So yes.

282
00:19:00.015 --> 00:19:01.140
Babysitter. sounds correct.

283
00:19:01.267 --> 00:19:02.350
Ah. man. not cool.

284
00:19:02.475 --> 00:19:04.562
Stay out of trouble. Lie low.

285
00:19:05.937 --> 00:19:10.067
Don't let Runa talk you
into a game of chance. She cheats.

286
00:19:11.818 --> 00:19:12.485
I do.

287
00:19:24.163 --> 00:19:25.915
Please. just listen.
This is all Zaya's fault.

288
00:19:26.250 --> 00:19:28.377
And unlike you guys. I'm actually
trying to find my brother.

289
00:19:28.502 --> 00:19:29.545
All right. yeah.

290
00:19:30.253 --> 00:19:32.297
We got it all down in your statement.

291
00:19:32.838 --> 00:19:34.048
Convincing stuff.

292
00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:39.930
You'll never find your brother.

293
00:19:42.390 --> 00:19:44.727
Especially if you listen to Zaya.

294
00:19:45.102 --> 00:19:48.522
Officer. I can't be in here.
This man tried to kill me.

295
00:19:48.647 --> 00:19:49.857
Officer!

296
00:19:52.567 --> 00:19:55.445
Who are you? And what
have you done with my brother?

297
00:20:00.742 --> 00:20:01.868
That's it.

298
00:20:03.495 --> 00:20:06.415
♪ Tommy used to work on the docks. ♪

299
00:20:07.332 --> 00:20:08.792
♪ union's been on strike ♪

300
00:20:09.083 --> 00:20:11.670
♪ He's down on his luck. it's tough. ♪

301
00:20:14.338 --> 00:20:16.048
♪ so tough ♪

302
00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:21.847
♪ We've gotta hold on to what we've got ♪

303
00:20:22.055 --> 00:20:25.683
♪ It doesn't make a difference
if we make it or not ♪

304
00:20:25.808 --> 00:20:30.897
♪ We've got each other
and that's a lot for love ♪

305
00:20:31.940 --> 00:20:33.483
♪ We'll give it a shot ♪

306
00:20:33.608 --> 00:20:37.528
♪ Whoa. we're half way there ♪

307
00:20:37.653 --> 00:20:41.157
♪ Whoa. Oh. Living on a prayer. ♪

308
00:20:41.783 --> 00:20:43.827
You didn't tell me the boy is a bard.

309
00:20:43.952 --> 00:20:44.787
♪ I swear. ♪

310
00:20:45.703 --> 00:20:48.832
♪ Oh! Living on a prayer. ♪

311
00:20:48.957 --> 00:20:52.335
♪ Living on a prayer. ♪

312
00:20:58.925 --> 00:21:00.302
Thank you. Thank you.

313
00:21:00.802 --> 00:21:03.597
That was a little ditty I
wrote dedicated to my gal. Runa.

314
00:21:03.722 --> 00:21:05.598
Runa! Give it up for Runa!

315
00:21:07.100 --> 00:21:10.270
Are you mad? I told you to
lie down and keep out of trouble.

316
00:21:10.395 --> 00:21:11.897
No. this is what got me out of trouble.

317
00:21:12.022 --> 00:21:14.607
You see. I bumped into this
huge. killer hairy guy. Thraxus.

318
00:21:14.733 --> 00:21:16.360
He's like the bouncer here.

319
00:21:16.485 --> 00:21:18.612
I spilled his mead so he was raging.

320
00:21:18.737 --> 00:21:20.447
I didn't have any
money by Thraxus' new drink.

321
00:21:20.572 --> 00:21:23.450
So I asked Ulfr.
he's like the owner. right?

322
00:21:23.575 --> 00:21:25.952
If I could earn a quick
few bucks by singing a song.

323
00:21:26.077 --> 00:21:28.372
And I kind of got up here
and I started playing for my life.

324
00:21:28.497 --> 00:21:29.580
Like. for real.

325
00:21:29.707 --> 00:21:31.542
And I started with
some easy hits. you know?

326
00:21:31.667 --> 00:21:32.458
some Lewis Capaldi. little Ed Sheeran.

327
00:21:32.583 --> 00:21:36.295
From what little... I understand every
detail of this story was a terrible idea.

328
00:21:36.422 --> 00:21:39.173
No. no. no. They were
vibing with Castle on the Hill.

329
00:21:39.298 --> 00:21:42.760
But then I pulled out some
bangers from my dad's old playlist.

330
00:21:42.885 --> 00:21:47.015
A little Guns N' Roses. some
Bon Jovi. and man. they went nuts.

331
00:21:47.140 --> 00:21:49.642
And you! Where were you for all of this?

332
00:21:49.768 --> 00:21:52.645
Runa is my manager.
She gets 10% of what I make.

333
00:21:52.770 --> 00:21:53.022
Half.

334
00:21:53.147 --> 00:21:54.355
Did you not understand what I said?

335
00:21:54.480 --> 00:21:56.148
Vedric has eyes everywhere.

336
00:21:56.273 --> 00:21:58.527
Come on. You gotta relax. Calibro.

337
00:21:58.652 --> 00:21:59.318
Calibro?

338
00:21:59.652 --> 00:22:02.655
I know Vedric has
eyes everywhere. but...

339
00:22:03.907 --> 00:22:05.158
I have the hearts.

340
00:22:05.283 --> 00:22:06.702
Okay. these thugs love me.

341
00:22:06.827 --> 00:22:07.493
Just be quiet.

342
00:22:07.618 --> 00:22:09.287
You can't blame a little
Bon Jovi. Just blew their mind.

343
00:22:09.412 --> 00:22:10.122
- Psh.
- Okay.

344
00:22:11.623 --> 00:22:13.958
I have the supplies.
so let's get back to the sanctuary.

345
00:22:14.083 --> 00:22:16.210
Yeah. it's gonna have to be a pass.

346
00:22:16.335 --> 00:22:17.337
I'm not going.

347
00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:22.092
Ulfr says my room and
meals are comped if I keep playing.

348
00:22:22.217 --> 00:22:24.510
It's like having my own
Las Vegas residency.

349
00:22:24.635 --> 00:22:28.932
To be clear. you used to stay
here rather than pursue the crown of Oleg.

350
00:22:29.057 --> 00:22:31.935
I know I'm the chosen warrior.
but Oaklee made

351
00:22:32.060 --> 00:22:34.562
me realize that our
team is more than covered.

352
00:22:34.687 --> 00:22:40.027
So just swing by and pick me up on
your way back from Oleg's dungeon thing.

353
00:22:40.652 --> 00:22:42.278
This is where I belong.

354
00:22:45.032 --> 00:22:46.700
Best of luck to you.

355
00:22:49.452 --> 00:22:54.290
You could have at least pretended
to be disappointed. Super hurtful!

356
00:22:59.670 --> 00:23:01.757
All right. the bard is back!

357
00:23:05.677 --> 00:23:09.263
And that was the last
I saw of those three whelps.

358
00:23:09.765 --> 00:23:11.600
Flynn and his
buddies didn't just disappear.

359
00:23:11.725 --> 00:23:14.602
They're not in another world
and there's no such thing as magic.

360
00:23:14.727 --> 00:23:16.395
They used my void key.

361
00:23:16.980 --> 00:23:19.607
And what did you do?
Attack them with that sword?

362
00:23:19.732 --> 00:23:24.362
I swear by the seven stars of
the Aishi. I laid not a finger upon them.

363
00:23:24.487 --> 00:23:26.907
It was I who was
wronged by your thieving brother.

364
00:23:27.032 --> 00:23:27.907
Fine.

365
00:23:28.032 --> 00:23:29.952
Then where is my thieving brother?

366
00:23:30.077 --> 00:23:31.327
And don't say across the stars.

367
00:23:31.453 --> 00:23:32.328
Across the stars.

368
00:23:32.453 --> 00:23:35.373
It's the same stupid story Zaya told me.

369
00:23:36.917 --> 00:23:42.422
She may see the future. but she will
distort the truth to serve her own ends.

370
00:23:43.257 --> 00:23:44.715
Tell me about it.

371
00:23:44.842 --> 00:23:48.678
She totally set me up. That's the
whole reason I'm in here.

372
00:23:48.803 --> 00:23:50.805
Zaya always has a reason.

373
00:23:50.930 --> 00:23:53.642
She of the inner eye cannot be trusted.

374
00:23:54.225 --> 00:23:56.603
Okay. Just level with me though.

375
00:23:57.395 --> 00:24:01.650
This is all some kind of
dorky game. right? Like a LARPing thing?

376
00:24:02.400 --> 00:24:04.735
You and Zaya know Flynn
through Discord or something?

377
00:24:04.862 --> 00:24:07.863
There is discord
only between Zaya and me.

378
00:24:08.030 --> 00:24:10.908
Your brother is
merely a pawn in her game.

379
00:24:11.033 --> 00:24:12.118
So it is all a game?

380
00:24:12.243 --> 00:24:15.872
There is no game. You
humans are so small minded.

381
00:24:16.665 --> 00:24:21.795
Your world is so full of wonders. yet you
cannot believe in the power of magic.

382
00:24:21.920 --> 00:24:25.048
I have a spell
that could crush your head.

383
00:24:27.675 --> 00:24:32.013
Well. if magic is real. why
don't you just magic your way out of here?

384
00:24:32.138 --> 00:24:34.015
Oh. I most certainly will.

385
00:24:35.642 --> 00:24:37.935
As soon as I get my maro back.

386
00:24:38.312 --> 00:24:43.942
those wretched watchman stole it from
me. but they will pay for their insolence!

387
00:24:44.108 --> 00:24:46.110
Yeah. I'm gonna stop talking to you now.

388
00:24:46.235 --> 00:24:47.737
Suit yourself. human.

389
00:24:48.280 --> 00:24:52.575
You will never save your
brother until you accept the truth.

390
00:24:56.663 --> 00:24:59.040
Calibor! Has anyone seen Calibor?

391
00:24:59.540 --> 00:25:01.375
Oh. there you are.

392
00:25:03.002 --> 00:25:03.878
Crushed it.

393
00:25:04.170 --> 00:25:05.213
Crushed what?

394
00:25:05.463 --> 00:25:08.592
Your list. I mean. not all
the items are found in the larder.

395
00:25:08.717 --> 00:25:10.218
but I figured it out.

396
00:25:11.218 --> 00:25:12.720
Mission accomplished.

397
00:25:12.887 --> 00:25:15.223
Impressive. Hand it over.

398
00:25:20.312 --> 00:25:21.938
Careful with the knife.

399
00:25:22.563 --> 00:25:25.525
Sister Aronya showed
me how to use the grindstone.

400
00:25:25.650 --> 00:25:27.527
I got it nice and sharp for you.

401
00:25:27.652 --> 00:25:30.655
Well done. my
brave and worthy apprentice.

402
00:25:35.035 --> 00:25:36.077
That was the mission.

403
00:25:37.203 --> 00:25:38.913
Get you stuff to make a sandwich?

404
00:25:39.038 --> 00:25:41.165
Do not disparage your own fine work.

405
00:25:41.290 --> 00:25:43.167
This is an excellent meal.

406
00:25:44.752 --> 00:25:45.420
Unreal.

407
00:25:45.628 --> 00:25:46.295
I know.

408
00:25:46.503 --> 00:25:49.215
Tyr-Valen bread is known
to be the softest in all the realm.

409
00:25:49.340 --> 00:25:52.552
So. all you did was
give me pointless busy work?

410
00:25:52.677 --> 00:25:53.428
Not at all.

411
00:25:53.553 --> 00:25:55.305
There's a very
important lesson in here somewhere.

412
00:25:55.430 --> 00:25:57.348
I just have to think of it.

413
00:25:57.473 --> 00:26:01.853
So. basically. I was your personal door
dash while you were off prepping my quest.

414
00:26:01.978 --> 00:26:03.103
It is not your quest.

415
00:26:03.228 --> 00:26:04.647
Yeah. because you stole it from me.

416
00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:06.232
Are all children from
your world raised to think

417
00:26:06.357 --> 00:26:07.817
that everyone knows
you friendship and good will?

418
00:26:07.942 --> 00:26:10.778
That the rest of us are here to coddle you
and make all your dreams come true.

419
00:26:10.903 --> 00:26:13.407
I don't want to be coddled. I
just want you to treat me as an equal.

420
00:26:13.532 --> 00:26:16.660
But you are not an equal.
And you never will be.

421
00:26:16.785 --> 00:26:20.955
At least Cash had enough sense to realise
how burdensome he is to the mission.

422
00:26:22.373 --> 00:26:23.248
Where is Cash?

423
00:26:23.375 --> 00:26:24.792
Oh. he's a bard now.

424
00:26:25.710 --> 00:26:26.377
He's a bard.

425
00:26:26.502 --> 00:26:28.212
He refused to return
from Bleak Wallow with me.

426
00:26:28.338 --> 00:26:30.090
And you just left him there?

427
00:26:30.215 --> 00:26:30.882
Yes.

428
00:26:31.298 --> 00:26:32.800
To improve our chances of success.

429
00:26:32.925 --> 00:26:34.385
This quest isn't
about you three children.

430
00:26:34.510 --> 00:26:36.847
It's quite literally about
saving the world.

431
00:26:36.972 --> 00:26:38.765
Yeah. I know. But Zaya said that...

432
00:26:38.890 --> 00:26:39.848
You will forgive me if I do not put my

433
00:26:39.975 --> 00:26:42.310
trust in the fantasies of a
capricious seeress.

434
00:26:42.435 --> 00:26:46.563
Honestly. meeting you three just proves
Zaya's predictions are mere delusion.

435
00:26:46.690 --> 00:26:48.733
Cash is no warrior.
Oaklee is no sorceress.

436
00:26:48.858 --> 00:26:51.695
And you are no legendary
thief nor a fearless leader.

437
00:26:51.820 --> 00:26:55.365
You are all nothing more than spoiled
selfish children away on a holiday.

438
00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:56.532
And I am not a ba...

439
00:26:56.658 --> 00:26:58.577
... babysitter.

440
00:26:59.535 --> 00:27:00.287
Am I saying that right?

441
00:27:00.412 --> 00:27:01.328
You're fired.

442
00:27:01.663 --> 00:27:02.330
Pardon?

443
00:27:02.497 --> 00:27:04.873
You are officially
fired as my Jedi master.

444
00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:06.583
If that means I am
no longer your mentor.

445
00:27:06.710 --> 00:27:09.128
I should like to point
out I never was to begin with.

446
00:27:09.253 --> 00:27:13.048
You know what? It's funny how you can just
sit there and call the three of us

447
00:27:13.173 --> 00:27:16.302
selfish when all
you care about is yourself.

448
00:27:16.510 --> 00:27:18.722
Enjoy the sandwich.

449
00:27:34.612 --> 00:27:36.823
Okay. pal. You are free to go.

450
00:27:38.282 --> 00:27:42.328
Alas. bring me my skull
and my vial of maro at once.

451
00:27:42.620 --> 00:27:44.413
Not you. Fruit Loop. You.

452
00:27:45.290 --> 00:27:50.212
Wretched round here. You shall rue the day
that you crossed paths with Goran.

453
00:27:50.337 --> 00:27:52.505
I already do. See you never. hopefully.

454
00:27:52.630 --> 00:27:56.050
Zaya will use and
betray you just as she did me.

455
00:28:05.560 --> 00:28:08.187
Cash seriously
wants us to leave him behind.

456
00:28:08.312 --> 00:28:12.525
Apparently. And for some
insane reason he's gone full bard.

457
00:28:13.652 --> 00:28:15.237
Maybe I'm the reason.

458
00:28:16.528 --> 00:28:19.782
He was just being such a big baby
when one thing wouldn't come easy to him.

459
00:28:19.907 --> 00:28:21.743
You know. in school I
always thought he was

460
00:28:21.868 --> 00:28:23.953
like this charm
dude with the perfect life.

461
00:28:24.078 --> 00:28:27.082
But he is just as
lost and insecure as us.

462
00:28:27.623 --> 00:28:30.335
When you say it like that. I feel bad.

463
00:28:31.127 --> 00:28:32.003
Séideadh.

464
00:28:33.672 --> 00:28:36.048
How does she do it
with just a single grain?

465
00:28:36.173 --> 00:28:38.258
Um... what do you do exactly?

466
00:28:39.010 --> 00:28:42.805
Well. if you ask Sister Brendowyn.
I'm wasting maro.

467
00:28:45.015 --> 00:28:46.058
Séideadh.

468
00:28:47.685 --> 00:28:49.812
Whoa. That's cool.

469
00:28:50.272 --> 00:28:54.358
I mean. this is my last day
here and this is all I've learned.

470
00:28:54.483 --> 00:28:56.027
Candle on. candle off.

471
00:28:56.152 --> 00:29:00.240
Oh. that's all? Back home
you'd be like a huge celebrity.

472
00:29:00.532 --> 00:29:02.033
Yeah. To nerds.

473
00:29:03.577 --> 00:29:04.577
Lasadh.

474
00:29:08.247 --> 00:29:09.540
So what do we do about Cash?

475
00:29:09.665 --> 00:29:12.793
We go get him
before he gets himself killed.

476
00:29:13.418 --> 00:29:14.420
The two of us?

477
00:29:16.297 --> 00:29:17.215
Lasadh.

478
00:29:19.383 --> 00:29:21.260
Seems like a job for Aurora and Kavan.

479
00:29:21.385 --> 00:29:23.303
No. Cash needs his friends.

480
00:29:24.472 --> 00:29:25.848
We're the only ones
that can get through to him.

481
00:29:25.973 --> 00:29:28.017
It sounds like you just want to
prove a point to Calibor

482
00:29:28.142 --> 00:29:29.268
and your draging me into it.

483
00:29:29.393 --> 00:29:33.147
Yeah. of course. No one's gonna believe in
us unless we can do things on our own.

484
00:29:33.272 --> 00:29:34.565
And why do I care
what people think of us?

485
00:29:34.982 --> 00:29:40.488
Well. my brother always said that I
play my video games to escape real life.

486
00:29:40.655 --> 00:29:41.530
Clearly.

487
00:29:41.655 --> 00:29:44.908
No. I loved it. I mean.
I was able to pull off

488
00:29:45.033 --> 00:29:47.953
legendary things no
one has ever done before.

489
00:29:48.078 --> 00:29:49.705
Yeah. In a game.

490
00:29:50.498 --> 00:29:53.125
Yeah. well. it's
time to level up in real life.

491
00:29:53.250 --> 00:29:58.590
But I can't prove anything
unless I have my team. The three of us.

492
00:30:03.177 --> 00:30:03.970
Fine.

493
00:30:05.555 --> 00:30:07.682
Lead the way. fearless leader.

494
00:30:08.558 --> 00:30:09.225
Séideadh.

495
00:30:13.688 --> 00:30:16.273
You have to teach me how to do that.

496
00:30:21.362 --> 00:30:26.617
You know. I should stay.
Like. do you have solitary confinement?

497
00:30:27.827 --> 00:30:30.497
You got this.

498
00:30:35.960 --> 00:30:38.588
I never thought I'd say this. but this
place is sketchier than my trailer park.

499
00:30:39.338 --> 00:30:42.467
Do I really think
Cash is gonna be in there?

500
00:30:47.513 --> 00:30:50.558
You held me down. but I got up

501
00:30:50.683 --> 00:30:52.560
Already brushing off the dust

502
